  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "They compassed me about also with words of hatred",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The hatred of the wicked for the good is a plain fact of history, and quite indisputable. \"Words of hatred\" are less patent, since they are often restrained from prudential considerations. But sometimes free vent is given to them (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 16:5-8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And fought against me without a cause",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 35:7, 19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 69:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 119:161",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Saul's hatred towards David was markedly of this character - un-provoked by either act or word from its object. Psalm 109:3",
        "children": []
